4️⃣ Feature Scaling
 
5️⃣ Train Logistic Regression Model
 
6️⃣ Make Predictions on the Test Set

🎯 Expected Output
Example output of predicted vs actual purchase decisions:

Predicted Purchases: [0 1 0 1 1 ...]  
Actual Purchases:    [0 1 0 1 0 ...]  
📜 Notes

Logistic Regression is used for binary classification (0 or 1).
Feature scaling helps standardize input variables for better model performance.
The dataset is split into training (80%) and testing (20%) for better evaluation.
